<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="248" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20437/96.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-06"><hi rend="italic">June 6,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Answering your June 1. Apparently impossible to procure repeal of potash
                            law, passed with full knowledge of our views. I suggest immediate
                            request for most favorable conditions obtainable from Bundesrat under
                            section 46.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>